## OWASP Top 10 baseline (already on)

Even in skeleton form, these defenses are NOT negotiable:

- **A01 Broken Access Control** ‚Äî every authoritative check lives on the Django side. Add client-side guards as UX only.
- **A02 Crypto Failures** ‚Äî session cookies (HttpOnly) are the only credential. NEVER store a JWT in `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` ‚Äî that's an XSS-to-takeover gun.
- **A03 Injection / XSS** ‚Äî React auto-escapes; `react/no-danger` ESLint rule bans the raw-HTML API.
- **A05 Misconfig** ‚Äî Vite proxies `/api` + `/_allauth` to Django so cookies stay first-party; never enable wildcard CORS.
- **A06 Vulnerable Components** ‚Äî pin majors in `package.json`; run `pnpm audit --prod` in CI; let Renovate update.
- **A08 Integrity** ‚Äî `pnpm-lock.yaml` committed; no `latest` tags.
- **A09 Logging** ‚Äî server-side; the SPA never logs request bodies (no credentials in console).

