## Calling the backend

The Vite proxy makes `/api/*` and `/_allauth/*` first-party requests. From any component:

```tsx
const me = await fetch("/api/me", {
  credentials: "include",   // session cookie
}).then((r) => r.json());
```

If your project uses **Django Ninja** (`api_layer = ninja`), the backend uses `django_auth` ‚Äî session-based. See [django-ninja auth docs](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/).
If it uses **DRF** (`api_layer = drf`), the backend uses `SessionAuthentication` ‚Äî see [DRF auth docs](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/).

In both cases the session cookie from `/_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login` is the only thing you need.
